sec.p:
For determining the energy budget of potato production, the amount of each input [tractor, disc harrow, diesel, human labour, bullock, potato seed, fertilizer (N, P and K), water for irrigation, insecticide and sprayer] was considered for common energy input. Cultivar and fertilizer (as per treatment) were considered for treatment energy input, while output energy was calculated considering the economic produce, i.e. seed. For estimating the energy value, quantity of different inputs and output was converted to energy by multiplying the respective energy equivalents (Table 1). The machine energy was calculated as per Devasenapathy et al. (2009) with some changes as follows:Table 1
